{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Change the curriculum\u00a0to provide greater mental health support in education.",
        "additional_details": "Bang The Desk is petitioning the government to make the following changes to the UK school\u00a0curriculum:\r\n\r\n1. Remove formal testing for anyone under the age of 18.\r\n\r\n2. Increase funding for the arts.\u00a0\r\n\u200b\r\n3. Introduce an hour of wellbeing into the curriculum every day.\r\n\r\n4. Start and end every school day with 10 minutes of mindfulness.\r\n\r\n5.\u00a0Greater mental health support across all educational institutions; mandatory counselling once a month for every student.\r\n\u200b\r\n6. Better wages and support for teachers.",
        "background": "bangthedesk.com is campaigning to change the curriculum\u00a0and\u00a0reform the\u00a0education system.\r\n\r\nSuicide is the leading cause of death among young people in the UK; this peaks in exam season.\r\n\r\nWe can statistically prove the damaging affect of stress on young people, so why are we doing nothing to help?",
